\begin_layout Title
Hydrodynamic Synchronization of optically trapped micro-beads
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hydrodynamic interaction plays an important role in the dynamics of microscopic
 particles.
 In a simple experimental setup using two optical traps, trapping a microbead
 each, we study the response of the second bead when first bead is driven
 with periodic force.
 We have further developed a theory to study and analyzed the experimental
 results.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The force balance equation of the optically trapped bead is,
